XS-Vcs-Bzr: http://bzr.debian.org/pkg-telepathy/packages/unstable/telepathy-glib/

Package: libtelepathy-glib0
Architecture: any
Section: libs
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Telepathy framework - GLib connection manager library
 This package contains telepathy-glib, a GLib-based library for Telepathy
 components.
 .
 Telepathy is a D-Bus framework for unifying real time communication,
 including instant messaging, voice calls and video calls. It abstracts
 differences between protocols to provide a unified interface for
 applications.
 .
  Homepage: http://telepathy.freedesktop.org/wiki/

Package: libtelepathy-glib-dev
Architecture: any
Section: libdevel
Depends: libtelepathy-glib0 (= ${binary:Version}), libglib2.0-dev (>= 2.4), libdbus-glib-1-dev (>= 0.72)
Suggests: libtelepathy-glib-doc, libtelepathy-glib-unstable-dev
Conflicts: libtelepathy-glib-static-dev
Replaces: libtelepathy-glib-static-dev
Description: GLib Telepathy connection manager library (headers)
 This package contains development files for telepathy-glib, a GLib-based
 library for Telepathy connection managers.
 .
 telepathy-glib cannot yet be used to write Telepathy clients - use
 libtelepathy for that.
 .
 Some interfaces are not yet considered API- and ABI-stable. To
 use those interfaces in your connection manager, you'll also need
 the static library telepathy-glib-unstable, found in the Debian package
 libtelepathy-glib-unstable-dev.
 .
 Telepathy is a D-Bus framework for unifying real time communication,
 including instant messaging, voice calls and video calls. It abstracts
 differences between protocols to provide a unified interface for
 applications.
 .
  Homepage: http://telepathy.freedesktop.org/wiki/

